                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="4" spanname="SPAN1">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Manifold Absolute Pressure (MAP) Sensor Voltage Checks</emph>
                                    (check with key-ON engine-OFF)
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="4" spanname="SPAN1">
                                <para>Install the 3 wire breakout tee between the MAP sensor and harness connector. View
                                    MAP VOLTAGE using the
                                    <emph type="bold">Continuous Monitor</emph>
                                    test found under the diagnostics menu in MASTER DIAGNOSTICS. If the circuit has an
                                    active fault according to the voltage level (Code 121 &#60;4.9V, Code 122 &#60;0.039V,
                                    Code 123
                                    <emph type="underscr">></emph>1.0 V), complete the following steps. Tests must be
                                    performed in order.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Test Condition</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
